<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id78c03f37-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s634e"><num value="634e">§ 634e.</num><heading> Assistance of Government agencies</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Each department, agency, and instrumentality of the Federal Government is authorized and directed to furnish to the Chief Counsel for Advocacy such reports and other information as he deems necessary to carry out his functions under sections 634a to 634g of this title.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id78c03f38-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/94/305/tII/s205">Pub. L. 94–305, title II, § 205</ref>, <date date="1976-06-04">June 4, 1976</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/90/670">90 Stat. 670</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id78c03f39-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id78c03f3a-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id78c03f3b-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was not enacted as part of the Small Business Act which comprises this chapter.</p>
</note>
